SLOW DOWN, LOOK UP 👆🐌✨⁣
At a time when Mother Nature is slowing down (in the Northern Hemisphere), our society paradoxically speeds up. ⁣
⁣
Rooting to a slower, more nature-bonded rhythm in the beginning of the month helps me find my center and peace throughout the entire holiday season. ⁣
⁣
To that end, I've created The seven-day, FREE Slow Down, Look Up Challenge to help you root to that slower, more intentional pace. And to help you and your family find your connection in the chaos.  I'm proud of the offerings that I give and try to make them simple, yet meaningful. ⁣
⁣
Inside you'll find:⁣
⁣
✨ Two ideas a day, for an entire week, one for slowing down and one for looking up.⁣
⁣
✨ Each day also includes extra relevant resources that I have found to be useful in my own life.⁣
⁣
✨ An art print to help inspire you to maintain the practice ⁣
⁣
I am looking forward to slowing down with your family!⁣
⁣
You can sign up in my bio. ⁣
⁣
Yours,⁣
⁣
Nicolette

Tomorrow is a special day. It's the last full of our year. We honor so many holidays and yet the moon, one of our most constant (even in her phases) companions, is there with us throughout the wild wheel we walk each year.⁣
⁣
This last full moon rises on Wednesday at 11:09 pm EST. ⁣
⁣
I hope your family gets a moment to slow down, look up and acknowledge all that has come into its fullest expression of being this year. ⁣
⁣
When we make it a priority to reflect and integrate together as a family, it invites our children to maintain that practice in their lives, even after we're gone. ⁣
⁣
What a gift to give them the encouragement and permission to take all the time they need to integrate their own precious, sacred human experience.⁣
⁣
🌕 If you are interested in aligning your family/community to the lunar cycles and this intention, The Kids Moon Club is now open to new 2023 members.⁣ Link in bio. 
⁣
My hope with the Club is of course to welcome more joy and celebrate, but also to help families align to a clock that is so much more nourishing than just a square on the wall. Together, we can find the wisdom waiting there. ⁣~ Yours, Nicolette #wildschooling #wilderchild #fullmoon #kidsmoonclub 
⁣

Experiences vs. things. It's so so hard to fight the tidal wave of consumption that happens this time of year. ⁣
⁣
Gift-giving is one of my big love languages, so I struggle with this all the time. I try to buy and support artisans, makers and small businesses & love finding the PERFECT gift. ⁣
⁣
But, it's always good to ground myself in the research and also the essence of what it means to be human. To be human is to share and create energy. Nothing holds energy and memory like sensory, connected experience. ⁣
⁣
Shared experience and tradition are the stitches in the fabric that enfolds us all. ⁣💕
⁣
Walking with that truth doesn't mean that I will never buy another gift. It just means that the things (yes, even if they are things!) rooted in that more connective intention will always shine brighter. ✨⁣🌕
⁣
Are any of your gifts experiences this year? I would love to hear!⁣
-----⁣
⁣
If you are interested in gifting a year-long, memory-making journey around the moon, The Kids Moon Club 2023 Journey is only open to new members until December 31st. Link in bio...⁣
⁣
If you have any questions, please let me know! ⁣
⁣
Yours,⁣
⁣
Nicolette⁣ #kidsmoonclub #gifts #wildschooling #wilderchild

You may or may not have heard but reactions to the AI (artificial intelligence) language model, ChatGPT are all over the internet. No a chat bot didn’t have to write this but from what I’ve seen it could come darn close!

Yes, tech fads come and go, but in the last two weeks there has been an explosion in the use and scaling of these AI technologies. From the image-generating DALL.E to Google's Lensa AI, they are multiplying by the day. 

SO what does this have to do with us, the nature-loving parents & caregivers? 

Well that's what Sunday's talk will be about. I'm definitely not an expert on the topic, but I'm curious and know that I want to be informed about this changing landscape and how it relates to my children’s future.

I'll be talking about this LIVE right here & covering:

- What these chatbots are

- Their various potential impacts on education, the future landscape 

- How and why it's important to stay aware of these new technologies. 
 
I would love to hear your thoughts & questions in the comments below ahead of this chat 👇🏽yours, Nicolette

Let's talk Slow parenting in the midst of the rapid emergence of AI - artificial intelligence. 
⁣
Yes, you're in the right place - we're discussing the emergence of artificial intelligence and what that means for parents. ⁣
⁣
In this chat I cover:⁣
⁣
- Dall-e 2, Chat GTP and other generative AIs ⁣
⁣
- Some of the ways these technologies are being used⁣
⁣
- How I'm approaching this brave new world with my children. ⁣
⁣
Also, at the end I talk about The Kids Moon Club and how our existing creations fit into all this!⁣
⁣
If you have any questions or thoughts, please comment below. ⁣#chatgtp #parenting #wildschooling #technology 
⁣
Yours, ⁣
⁣
Nicolette

When I provide an offering like The Kids Moon Club, it's not just about me. It's about creating something that families and communities can step into and create their own culture within. ⁣
⁣
Culture is the beating heart of humanity. And for thousands of years humans have been co-creating with Mother Nature and each other. ⁣
⁣
This moon box is the perfect example of creating off the page. One of the current members made and presented this moon box that held the characters, membership card, and other goodies to inspire a year's worth of alignment with nature's rhythms. ⁣🌕✨
⁣
If you are interested in stepping into an experience that lives and breathes - that puts culture and creation at its center, the doors to the Kids Moon Club are open for four more days. Link in bio. ⁣
⁣
~ Your sojourner with nature, ⁣
⁣
Nicolette

Every year, rather than a resolution (that I know I won't be able to fulfill!), I choose a word to anchor to. It serves as a golden thread that I can hold onto for the entire year. ⁣⁣✨
⁣⁣
This year, mine is, Co-create. Mother Nature is always inviting me to surrender just a little bit more, to make space and invite in a larger, wiser more co-creative energy. It takes a lot to let go of the ego and to tune to that pure intention over just pushing with my own will. We'll see how it goes! ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I'd love to hear what your word is. What is on your heart right now? What word rings true for your vision ahead?⁣⁣ 🌿🦋#wordoftheyear 
⁣⁣

Threshold moments are so powerful. As we stand on the edges, our ability to hold the space in between can be difficult. ⁣
⁣
May this year you know you are not alone. 
⁣
May you know you are held within a wilder, wiser circle. ⁣
⁣
And may you be invited to surrender over and over again, to stretch your edges & your capacity to face the shadow.  ⁣
⁣
Sometimes the calendar year can be synonymous for me with the confines of norms, expectations, jobs - with human constraints and constructions. ⁣
⁣
Which is why I root to Mother Nature before going out into the world. This orientation is a skill that can be learned! ⁣
⁣
This knowing and way of being is more important than math, reading or writing. And much like language acquisition, embodying this knowledge early in life, means our children can feel that flow in all that they do! ⁣✨💕
⁣
Everything I create is in service to cultivating and cocreating with that higher state of consciousness. ⁣
⁣
And the Kids Moon Club is the most complete offering for children and families that I have brought into this world. ⁣
⁣
If you feel this year is the year to prioritize that path and way of walking...if you feel your children can benifit from getting on moon time. ⁣
⁣
Then please join me and others who have made this commitment. Doors close tonight at MIDNIGHT. ⁣
⁣
Happy new calendar year, may you bring more and more of yourself to the light. ⁣🌕
⁣
Yours,⁣
⁣
Nicolette⁣
⁣

⁣
When we all align and turn our voices to the sky it allows us to feel our unique power and our connection to the collective pulse of all life. ⁣
⁣
And the more we do it, the more we give our children permission to do the same. ⁣
⁣
Happy Full Moon, what are you howling for?⁣
⁣
Yours, ⁣
⁣

Also the Kids Moon Club is closed for the year, but if you want to get on the waitlist for 2024 and receive a year’s worth of inspiration, you can do that at the link in my bio. #kidsmoonclub #wildschooling #wilderchild #fullwolfmoon #fullmoon

There is so much talk about helping kids stay creative, but humans learn best, like fish in water, from the culture they’re swimming in. ⁣
⁣
But, it’s so hard to be creative sometimes because, we need time to root ourselves to that force and flow. And our most scarce and precious resource is time. ⁣
⁣
And that’s why when I see my husband’s creations, experiments and ideas (in this case what he calls the Bird Man Hand, an effort to teach the birds to eat out of our hands) pop up around our house, I’m just so so glad. ⁣
⁣
It shows my kids that we’re still learning, we’re still playing, we’re still trying to co-create and collaborate with Mother Nature. ⁣
⁣
Hopefully, they will always be able to find the time for that wild connection. ⁣
⁣
Yours, ⁣
⁣
Nicolette
Believe our children when they see the wonder, and the wonder will grow. ✨

I remember buying this when the girls were young, it sat in our pole barn - just another item I had spontaneously purchased without quite thinking about timing or intent - it just looked so cool! I’ve done that a lot. I can be so far out ahead of myself, I’m behind ha! ⁣
⁣
But, it’s nice to see something come into fruition, to witness a little seed that we thought was dead, suddenly come up so unexpectedly. ⁣
⁣
It may seem like a small thing, making kindling, but it’s inviting my girls into their power, while also being in service to the family - and that is village-led learning. ⁣
⁣
Yours, ⁣
⁣
Nicolette #wildschooling #villageledlearning

Happy New Moon and what is colloquially known as the Snow Moon Cycle. Here is just a little window into how we mark the moment in our home. ⁣
⁣
These traditions and rituals tied to the cycles have been a hallmark of human culture for thousands of years. Acknowledging these points on the wheel turns our attention back to these important signposts on the journey, bringing us back into the circle of wild things...bringing us back home. ⁣
⁣
May you have a beautiful new moon and if you have the space, set intentions as a community and family.  ⁣🌑✨ #wildschooling #kidsmoonclub #newmoon
⁣
~ Yours, ⁣
⁣
Nicolette

Nature connection needs a conduit, especially for children and the most powerful thread that binds is relationship. My brother and sister in law, who are certified mushroom foragers, made this for my daughters & it inspires them to not only play, but to fall in love with mushrooms every time they get it out. 🍄✨ #wildschooling #games #gameschooling #art #handmade #mushrooms

Hello! I never really properly introduce myself here. Although most feedback I get is overwhelmingly beautiful, I'm often faced with feedback, comments and messages attacking and challenging me on various things. The grammar police are strong 🙂 Every interaction is sacred and considered deeply by me, even the hard ones. Thank you for being a part of this community and for connecting with the movement to co-parent and co-create with Mother Nature. Rebuilding and tuning to that relationship is my passion in this world. So here's something personal, this is my husband and our donkey Jazzy. My husband has supported my work in the world, which is a lot considering I'm a mom just trying to create in the margins. He does that most by caring for not only my tender heart, but all the wild ones (including our two growing girls) on our land. 

Now, tell me something about you! Something unique - something (however small) that shows who you are. ~ Yours, Nicolette

Happy New moon and start of the cycle colloquially known Worm Moon. ⁣⁣🐛🌑
⁣⁣
Our family and Wildschooling tunes to a circular, seasonal year running from Winter Solstice to Winter Solstice, with the lunar cycles, equinoxes and solstices serving as signposts throughout our yearly and life-long journey. ⁣
⁣⁣
The new moons are chances to start anew, with this one being a powerful one in the Northern Hemisphere as we're in a rising action (any time before the Summer Solstice) and we're also on the verge of Spring! In fact the last of this cycle (March 20th) holds within it the first day of spring! ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
It's often hard to attain that feeling of newness, but aligning and being able to renew ourselves is a skill set that children can use throughout their lives. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
With every returning bird, emerging sprout, and ephemeral flower we can hear Mother Nature singing to us - you are HERE and you have never been HERE in exactly this way before. ⁣⁣
May you and your family acknowledge and orient to this seasonal anchor. What are your intentions going forward? What will you carry, what will you compost and leave behind?⁣⁣
⁣⁣
~ Yours,⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Nicolette #newmoom
How to honor a maple tree before tapping. #gratitude #wildschooling #mapletapping #spring #natureeducation
A meditative journey towards finding the beauty in the varying weather & conditions that emerge in our lives. #wilderchild #homeschooling #celebrateseasonalshifts #thewildwheel

Happy Full Moon - colloquially called The Worm Moon.⁣⁣ 🪱🌕
⁣
This moon is the first cycle that will fall within the spring season (the last day of this cycle is the first day of spring!). ⁣
⁣
I often think about the ritual of spring cleaning and also like to extend that to my inner biome by doing a detox. But, before we get the urge to purge, I often think about trying to be present with what IS there. What wants to come out? I want to have a clear relationship, presence and understanding of those parts of myself. ⁣
⁣⁣
May you find a moment today or in the next three days to look up at the moon as a family or community - letting the light shine on ALL parts of you. 🪱🌕✨⁣⁣#wildschooling #wilderchild #wormmoon #celebrateseasonalshifts 
⁣⁣
Yours, ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Nicolette
Why do we have resistance to certain aspects of Mother Nature?

Happy Belated New Moon and start of what is colloquially called the Pink Moon. Our family has been so sick with a bad stomach bug, and so the new moon came and went without a proper acknowledgment on the day. ⁣
⁣
But, you know what, even if life stops us from marking the lunar and seasonal moments, the moments still come. ⁣🌸
⁣
It's so comforting - at a time when parents are expected to do it all, be picture perfect, to have ALL the things, to make ALL the crafts - to just rest in Mother Nature's rhythms...⁣
⁣
to just let ourselves be rocked by her waves, to let them wash over us and know we're being held and nourished even as we sleep. ⁣
⁣
I hope this new cycle has started out beautifully for you, what dreams would your family like to bring into this reality this cycle?⁣
⁣
Yours,⁣
⁣
Nicolette

It is said that when a moon forms itself in your tea or coffee that a vision you've hidden, even onto yourself, will emerge. 

Despite our society's insistence on facts and pragmatism - myth and magic persist. Signs, half human-half animal creatures, sirens, and fairies, waters that speak. Bigfoot foraging blackberries until our gaze startles it back into the wild.  

So many visions rising up from our collective unconscious. All the untamed, unbound aspects of ourselves that we cannot fully meet. 

If we turn our inner eyes towards them just a little, one day we might find messages rising up from the cup in our hands. 

What has Mother Nature revealed to you recently, in ways you might not yet fully understand? 🌙✨

It’s so hard not to ask a child what they are doing, but if we can just wait and dwell in the mystery it helps us to give space for what magic will unfold for them. 

And it reminds us to do the same for our own lives. #wildschooling #wilderchild #natureplay

Happy full often colloquially called the Pink Moon! Pink is such a soft, opening color. Paired with the full moon, it's a powerful invitation for myself and my family to see where we are protecting ourselves and armoring up. ⁣
⁣
How can we open just a little bit more, to be vulnerable and share the softer, gentler aspects of our nature?⁣ 🌸
⁣
I hope you and your family get a moment to tune to the full moon & welcome that brilliance into your life. ⁣
⁣
Yours,⁣
⁣
Nicolette #kidsmoonclub #pinkmoon #fullmoon #wildschooling

Happy New Moon and start to the (colloquially named), Flower Moon cycle.⁣ 🌸🌺🌷🌼 🌑
⁣
We're seeing the first dandelions, daffodils, violets and bloodroot come up. It's overwhelming after not seeing our beautiful friends in a year. ⁣
⁣
Flowers ask something of us in the encounter. ⁣
⁣
The amount of beauty we perceive outside of us is connected to our inner capacity to receive it. ⁣
⁣
And flowers in their infinite tenderness and glory invite us to open up more, to make room for that tremulous, co-creative encounter. ⁣
⁣
May you have a moment as a family to set your intentions, however small, for the cycle ahead! ⁣
⁣
I would love to hear the dreams you are hoping will open in the days ahead...⁣
⁣
Yours,⁣
⁣
Nicolette #newmoon #flowermoon #kidsmoonclub

Happy (colloquially called) Full Flower Moon! It's such a powerful alignment because it's also the astronomical midpoint between Spring and Summer in the Northern Hemisphere. ⁣
⁣
We haven't seen the dandelions in a year. And now suddenly here they are on the landscape. ⁣🌼🌼
⁣
What feels like it is "suddenly there" and appearing in you and your family's view? ⁣
⁣
These seasonal cycles and occurrences offer us a much-needed breath and space to notice what might otherwise get swept away in the current of our modern life. ⁣
⁣
May you have find that space, however small, for your family to see, celebrate and know yourself in a new, shimmering light. ⁣
⁣
Have a beautiful full moon. ⁣#flowermoon #kidsmoonclub #wildschooling #fullmoon 
⁣
Yours,⁣
⁣
Nicolette⁣

The simplest way to cook foraged foods is to just add them to recipes you already love. In this case, these Dutch Baby pancakes (there is a link in my bio to the recipe) are easy large & wonderful pancakes that the kids can’t get enough of. 
⁣
It’s so simple to just go outside, see what’s edible and blooming & throw it on! This approach encourages the kids to have a more accessible, inclusive relationship with nature. They will feel like they can go out and gather, adding the wild to everything from their grilled cheese sandwich to their shakes. ⁣
⁣
What is a recipe you have that you could add in a dash of the wild?⁣ 🌼🌸 
⁣
Yours,⁣
⁣
Nicolette #wilderchild #wildschooling #recipes #foraging #wildedibbles

Another lesson from Mother Nature. I’m often so focused on my own vision that I can’t see the abundance right in front of me. Here’s to a balance, here’s to a more co-creative way of seeing and growing together. #wildschooling #wilderchild #foraging #parenting

The calendar and our modern celebrations as they stand don't do much for helping us experience a full, contextual emotive journey through the year. ⁣
⁣
But we can curate and architect meaning and growth back into our lives. ⁣🌱❤️
⁣
One way to do that is by tuning to the same sky our ancestors did. Every lunar cycle, there are astronomical points that can serve as invitations to explore not only the wilder world around us but also the landscape within. ⁣
⁣
You can design this yourself, but if you need a little help I'm doing a giveaway of Mindfulness with the Moon - a 75 page offering that guides you through the emotive components of each lunar month of the year. You can look at my previous post on how to enter. ⁣
⁣
No matter what you anchor to, I hope your family continues to find ways to slow down, culture-build and co-create with your own life and seasonal year. ⁣✨🙏🍓
⁣
You deserve to have that sovereign and authentic experience. ⁣
⁣
Yours,⁣
⁣
Nicolette⁣
⁣

Just a little reminder from the red-wing blackbird babies today. ⁣
⁣
We can help our children notice when something in nature is inviting us to slow down and breathe. But before we do that, we must be able to recognize that moment for ourselves. ⁣
⁣
This is just a little reminder to attune to Mother Nature in the next couple of days and try to notice if there is a moment that carries that ineffable, resonant quality that for some mysterious reason, begs us to breathe. ⁣
⁣
Yours,⁣

I cannot express enough gratitude for the Indigenous people around the world and their living, diverse culture. More than inspiration, their lives have provided a path of reconciliation to walk. And while walking, it has awoken my own deep, Earth-rooted, ancestral connection.

I am forever grateful and bow deeply to their knowledge and relationship with the Earth since Time Immemorial. 

Below is the Haudenosaunee Thanksgiving Address, which I read to my children on this day. 

This address is also known as the "Words That Come Before All Else," is a traditional ceremonial greeting and acknowledgment practiced by the Haudenosaunee, also known as the Iroquois Confederacy. The Haudenosaunee is a group of indigenous nations in North America, including the Mohawk, Oneida, Onondaga, Cayuga, Seneca, and Tuscarora.

The Haudenosaunee Thanksgiving Address is a profound expression of gratitude, humility, and interconnectedness, emphasizing the importance of living in harmony with the natural world and one another. It reflects the deep spiritual and cultural values of the Haudenosaunee people and serves as a reminder of the sacredness of all life.

May gratitude spill forth from your heart like a river. 💚

Yours,

Nicolette #gratitude #thanksgiving #wildschooling #indigenous

to hear and harmonize just a little bit more of the collective song. ⁣

⁣
